# /usr/local/Cellar/
where the packages are installed
  ex. /usr/local/Cellar/sbt/1.1.6/
  ex. /usr/local/Cellar/scala/2.12.3/

# Shortcuts
(MAC)
Logout: Shift + Cmd + q
Lock screen: Control + Shift + Power/Eject
Close app: Cmd + q
Input source switch: Control + Option + Space (Cmd + Space)
Print screen: Command+Shift+ 3 (full screen) or 4 (region)

(MAC Texting)
1. Go to end of line: Cmd + right arrow (Control + right arrow)
2. Go to end of current or next word: Option + right arrow
3. Go to end of all the text: Cmd + down arrow

(MAC Terminal / Bash)
1. Go to line beginning: Shift + Fn + right arrow
2. Go to line end: Shift + Fn + right arrow
3. Remove command to the line beginning: Control + u
4. Remove command to the line end: Control + k 
5. Go to next word: Option + right arrow
6. Enter full screen: Cmd + Control + f
7. Delete a word backwards: Control + w
8. Delete a char backwards: Control + h
9. Copy the content of a file to your clipboard: pbcopy < filepath
10. Direct the content of the paste to stdout: pbpaste | grep keyword
11. Go to next tab: Shift + Cmd + } or right arrow
12. Get full hostname on Mac: host `hostname`

(MAC Terminal / Zsh)
1. Go to line beginning: Control + a
2. Go to line end: Control + e
3. Remove command to the line beginning: Control + u (but need to add a line "bindkey \^U backward-kill-line" to ~/.zshrc)

(Vim)
1. Go to line beginning: Fn + left arrow
2. Go to line end: Fn + right arrow
3. Go to next word: w (normal mode)
4. Page down: Fn + down arrow
5. Go to beginning/end of all the text: gg/G
* Go-End-of-Line
    * Vim: Fn + right arrow
    * MAC Terminal: Shift + Fn + right arrow
    * MAC Texting: Cmd + right arrow

(Chrome)
1. Go the the next tab page: Option + Cmd + right arrow
2. Open a new tab page: Cmd + t
3. Close the current tab page: Cmd + w
4. Enter full screen in chrome: Cmd + Shift + f

(Safari)
1. Go the the next tab page: Shift + Cmd + right arrow

(SSH Session)
1. Scroll up: Ctrl + a, then Esc, then up/down arrow or page up/down

(Screen)
Detach screen: Control + A, press d
Scroll/Copy Mode: Control + A, press ESC


